						<summary>

						<p>South wall of the central shrine in the Vēdapurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājakēsarivarmaṉ year 14: (Sundarachōḷa Parāntaka II).</hi></p>						

						<p>The record may be assigned to c. 10th century on palaeographical grounds. This incomplete record, registers the gift of money in <hi rend="italic">Iḻakkāśu</hi> made by Kuñjiramalli, the wife and daughter respectively of Śiṟiyavēḷāṉ, for burning lamps in the temple at Tirukkuḍittiṭṭai which was included in Amaninārāyaṇa-chaturvēdimaṅgalam. Śiṟiyavēḷāṉ is identical with Pirāntakaṉ Śiṟiyavēḷār, the general of the Chōḷa king Sundara-Chōḷa Parāntaka II.</p>						

						</summary>
